  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  🎓 LEARNING TIPS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  FOR PYTHON BEGINNERS:
    1. Write code in main.py
    2. Right Cmd + R to run it
    3. See output in terminal
    4. Use Right Cmd + I to experiment with new syntax
    5. When stuck: Right Cmd + D to debug step-by-step

  FOR VIM BEGINNERS:
    - Start with: hjkl for movement
    - Learn: i (insert), Esc (normal), v (visual)
    - Master: ciw (change word), dd (delete line)
    - Then learn: text objects (ci", ci(, cit)
    - Finally: vim.surround (S", cs'", dst)

  FOR REACT DEVELOPERS:
    - Space+; formats your code instantly
    - Space+i organizes imports automatically
    - gd jumps to component definition
    - gr shows all places component is used
    - Space+a for quick imports and fixes


